monica calif a longdistance runner who ran the great britain 
route in 1965 
it is the longest run yet for goodman whose past efforts have 
raised thousands of dollars for charities around the state the 
current run is not for charity he said the money is needed to pay 
for air fare a training van and pace car food and hotels 
in 1985 goodman ran 130 miles from the kingdome in seattle to 
the peace arch near blaine his boyhood home on the canadian 
border that raised 20000 for a nursing home in blaine 
next may he plans to run 2000 miles across the old pony 
express route from st joseph mo to san francisco 
