<TEXT>
chinas family planning policy which calls for 
no more than one child per couple has in six years reduced by 301 
million the number of children under the age of 14 the state 
statistics bureau said today 
the bureau said china now has 30715 million children under 14 
compared to 33725 million in 1982 
it found the proportion of children in chinas total population 
of 107 billion to be 2868 percent down from 3345 percent six 
years ago the official xinhua news agency reported 
the bureau attributed the decline to the family planning policy 
which has been largely successful in chinas crowded cities but has 
met resistance in many rural areas where two or more children is 
still the norm 
the bureau said children account for just 1836 percent of the 
population in shanghai chinas largest city while making up 36 
percent in the remote western areas of tibet and ningxia hui 
autonomous region 
