standing still at that particular point and why the engineer of 
the passenger train didnt see it or whether the signals failed 
meijer said 
the roosendaalvlissingen line is equipped with automatic 
signals 
both tracks were blocked by the wreckage of both trains meijer 
said adding that the damage to the line and the overhead power 
lines was considerable 
fatal train collisions are rare on the technically advanced 
dutch railway network which is one of the busiest in the world 
the last serious train accident occurred in december 1982 when 
three passengers were killed in a collision near the port city of 
