president reagan and soviet leader mikhail s 
gorbachev at an impasse this week on strategic arms negotiations 
celebrated a past summit success today by exchanging final 
ratification documents on last decembers pact on 
intermediaterange weapons 
but they deadlocked on the explosive issue of spacebased 
defenses and failed to take steps to cut concentrations of eastern 
and western troops in europe 
we have missed a chance to take an important step forward 
gorbachev told reporters 
while accusing reagan of incomprehensible maneuvers on 
conventional forces gorbachev also registered a lack of progress 
