george bushs flexible freeze 
plan to end the federal budget deficit by 1993 depends on an 
optimistic outlook and a reduction in interest rates by at least 2 
percentage points his economic advisers said wednesday 
we all concluded that a flexible freeze is the right way to 
go that is indeed doable said former deputy treasury secretary 
