with the applications of water treatment chemicals and biocides to 
the cooling tower he said 
legionnaires disease was first diagnosed in 1976 when 221 
people contracted it at an american legion convention in 
philadelphia it produces symptoms similar to pneumonia and often 
caused by bacteria from watercooled air conditioning units 
