three more people were arrested wednesday on 
charges that they were part of a scheme to mail cocaine to the 
united states from a us military post office in panama and 
officials said more arrests were expected 
the three georgian women arrested wednesday and two new york 
city women arrested last week appeared before a federal magistrate 
a sixth suspect the husband of one of the new york women was in 
custody in new york city 
authorities said the scheme came to light last week when a 
former soldier stopped for a traffic violation admitted that he 
was carrying cocaine and agreed to cooperate with police his 
information led to the arrests of the six 
colquitt county sheriff gene beard said investigators seized two 
packages of cocaine that were mailed to moultrie ga from the 
military post office in panama the drugs were to be taken from 
moultrie to new york city he said 
it was the fifth case in recent months in which drug smuggling 
from panama has been linked in some way with the us military 
presence there there are about 10000 us servicemen deployed in 
panama 
in december two civilian security guards who worked for the 
us navy in panama were arrested at kennedy international airport 
in new york city after customs agents allegedly found cocaine in 
their suitcases 
the other three cases all in late january or early february 
involved cocaine found on military airplanes flying out of panama 
or someone with drugs attempting to board such a plane 
in the most recent case beard said two packages of cocaine an 
18pound package seized from jackie lee bigelow of colquitt county 
on may 24 and a 29pound package seized friday at the moultrie post 
office had been mailed to moultrie from a military post office in 
panama 
army spokeswoman paige eversole in washington said investigators 
were in georgia on tuesday and planned to go from there to panama 
to investigate any military involvement in the cocaine shipments 
the army has investigations going on and has had for some 
time into drug trafficking by service members and by people posing 
as service members in panama she said there was no evidence so 
far that anyone on active duty was involved in the georgia scheme 
she said 
an fbi affidavit released wednesday said bigelow an informant 
told investigators he had traveled to panama twice this year to 
meet with two members of the drug operation he said he arranged 
for cocaine packages to be mailed to the three georgia women 
fbi agent david parker of macon said the drug operation appears 
to have been going on for some time and more arrests are 
expected 
we consider it a very significant investigation he said 
were investigating importation into this country by two methods 
handcarrying and mailing it 
parker said bigelow who was stationed in panama while serving 
in the army likely will face federal charges stemming from his 
alleged involvement in the operation the sheriff said he could 
also face state drug charges 
taken before us magistrate nathan davis in albany on wednesday 
were maxine williams 24 brenda mcgee 25 and betty howard 31 
all residents of colquitt county and regina carmela smith and 
julia thom both of new york city 
they were charged with conspiracy to possess cocaine with intent 
to distribute said assistant us attorney deborah fowler 
davis scheduled a bond hearing for the defendants thursday 
afternoon ms fowler said the government plans to argue that they 
should not be released 
ms smiths husband oscar smith was arrested in new york city 
on the same charge and is being held there said us attorney 
edgar w ennis jr who added that other warrants have been issued 
after he was arrested in the traffic case and agreed to 
cooperate with police bigelow called smith to arrange for couriers 
to pick up the cocaine in georgia the affidavit said ms smith 
and ms thom were arrested friday after they arrived in moultrie 
and met bigelow at a motel 
beard said it appeared that moultrie was one of several us 
towns where cocaine was mailed from panama he said he didnt know 
what measures would have been in effect at us military post 
offices in panama to prevent unauthorized people from mailing 
packages 
parker declined to say whether the two men named by bigelow in 
the affidavit ricardo brown and ferdson allister smith were in 
the military ferdson smith oscar smiths brother has been 
arrested in panama on unrelated drug charges 
its bound to be a larger operation but our man says he 
doesnt know any of the other players beard said 
