<TEXT>
floor brokers on the new york stock exchange 
posted their best year ever in 1987 despite the slashing of stock 
prices during the october market crash a published report said 
today 
quoting confidential exchange records the new york times said 
the 54 specialist firms collectively lost 1667 million in 
october but still managed to post profits of 3693 million before 
taxes for the year 
specialists are appointed by the exchange to make markets in 
individual stocks they are charged with making sure that market is 
orderly even if it means buying and selling equities from their 
own accounts 
they have been criticized for not doing more to smoothe out the 
market during the crash but specialist advocates have commended 
their performance during the crisis 
financial data on specialists are kept secret and are not 
reported to the securities and exchange commission because they are 
private enterprises the paper said 
the times said it obtained the data from congressional staff 
sources who received the confidential records from the exchange as 
part of a continuing investigation into the crash 
according to figures provided to the times specialists earned 
185 billion before taxes from 1981 through 1987 while their 
equity capital amounted to 923 million at the end of last year 
the times said that indicates they took out of their businesses 
138 billion not including salaries and expenses 
specialists returns have not dipped below 30 percent this 
decade the paper said 
meanwhile exchange members who deal with the public and are not 
specialists had capital of about 229 billion last year but their 
pretax return amounted to 48 percent the paper reported 
richard grasso presidentelect of the exchange noted that 
several new rules have been instituted to boost slightly the 
capital specialists must have on hand 
he told the times the earnings figures should have been lower 
because they did not take into account payments partners in the 
specialist firms made to themselves as a return on their 
investments 
