said i think were heading downhill in this industry and 
eventually the fate of the housing market will filter through 
the rest of the economy as well 
new homes need to be furnished with durable goods like 
refrigerators or washers and dryers he said 
the higher rates also threaten new construction contracts 
including residential and nonresidential units said christie 
fw dodge reported tuesday that contracting for new projects 
declined 6 percent in april from the previous month to an annual 
rate of 22697 billion extending a downward slide that began last 
fall 
bhristie said high vacancy rates in commercial properties 
particularly offices and apartments were responsible for reversing 
the industrys fiveyear upswing but he said rising interest rates 
will only aggravate the situation since they translate to higher 
borrowing costs for contractors 
the export boom which is pumping up the 1988 economy isnt 
much help to the construction industry and could even prove 
troublesome christie said as economic activity heats up 
rising interest rates imply still lower building later in the 
year 
