located about 270 miles to the northeast of tobolsk 
the western companies will receive payments in convertible 
currency for their design engineering and construction work and 
then will be invited to participate in a joint venture that 
actually will manufacture the petrochemicals hugel said 
the soviet ruble is not convertible making it difficult for 
foreign companies to export profits but the soviet union earns 
much of its hard currency through sales of oil and natural gas and 
certain ministries recently have been given the right to use hard 
currency as an incentive to attract foreign companies into joint 
ventures 
the plastics will be made both for soviet domestic use and for 
export officials said the percentage to be exported has not been 
determined but that most of the plastics may go to the domestic 
market if gorbachevs effort to stimulate consumer products is 
successful 
combustion engineering provides equipment and services for the 
power and process industries such as paper mills and oil 
refineries the company reported sales in 1987 of about 3 billion 
