burlington northern inc is the parent company of burlington 
northern railroad co the nations largest rail system with 
28000 miles of track stretching from the pacific northwest to the 
gulf of mexico bn is the thirdlargest corporation in washington 
state after boeing co and weyerhaeuser co 
bn was formed in 1970 with the merger of great northern railway 
northern pacific railway chicago burlington amp quincy railroad 
spokane portland amp seattle railway and pacific coast railroad 
since 1980 the company has diversified with ownership of a 
major natural gas pipeline between texas and california an oil and 
gas production company and real estate its holdings include some 
25 million acres of land 
bn had net income of 3693 million on revenues of 662 billion 
in 1987 
